      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">42.709-7</ph> Contract clause.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <p class="- topic/p " id="d2537e8">Use the clause at <xref href="52.242-3.dita#FAR_52_242_3"
                  base="FAR_52_242_3"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">52.242-3</xref>, Penalties for Unallowable Costs, in all solicitations and contracts over <ph rev="FAC 2025-06 October 1, 2025" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2024-001?>$1 million<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 42.709-7 by removing “$800,000” and adding “$1 million” in its place.?></ph> except fixed-price contracts without cost incentives or any firm-fixed-price contract for the purchase of commercial products or commercial services. Generally, covered contracts are those which contain one of the clauses at <xref href="52.216-7.dita#FAR_52_216_7"
                  base="FAR_52_216_7"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">52.216-7</xref>, <xref href="52.216-16.dita#FAR_52_216_16"
                  base="FAR_52_216_16"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">52.216-16</xref>, or <xref href="52.216-17.dita#FAR_52_216_17"
                  base="FAR_52_216_17"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">52.216-17</xref>, or a similar clause from an executive agency’s supplement to the FAR.</p>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
